-----------------------------------------
ANTI-PHISH EXTENSION – MANUAL TEST PROTOCOL
-----------------------------------------

# Step 1: Load Extension
1. Open chrome://extensions
2. Enable “Developer Mode”
3. Click “Load Unpacked”
4. Select Anti-Phish main folder

Expected: Extension loads successfully with icon visible.

-----------------------------------------------------

# Step 2: Open Demo Phishing Page
File: /demo/phishing-sample.html  
URL example:  
file:///D:/Anti-Phishing/demo/phishing-sample.html

Expected:
- Red warning banner appears automatically
- Background logs: “contains credential form”

-----------------------------------------------------

# Step 3: Test Dismiss
1. Click “Dismiss”
Expected: Banner disappears.

2. Open popup → click “Scan tab”
Expected: Banner reappears.

-----------------------------------------------------

# Step 4: Safe Sites Test
Visit:
- https://google.com
- https://github.com

Expected:
- No banner
- Background logs: “no issues found”

-----------------------------------------------------

# Step 5: Suspicious URL Test
Visit:  
https://secure-login.example.com  
https://account-verify-example.net

Expected:
- Should be flagged based on heuristic match

-----------------------------------------------------

# Step 6: Popup Functionality
1. Click “Scan Tab”  
2. Check popup status message

Expected:
- “Scanning tab…”
- then “Scan completed”
- Banner appears if page contains form

-----------------------------------------------------

# Step 7: Background Console Verification
Open service worker console:

chrome://extensions → Inspect views → service worker

Expected logs:
- “background service worker starting”
- “running checks”
- “sent showWarning”
- “no issues found” for safe URLs

-----------------------------------------------------

# Step 8: Code Reload Persistence
1. Reload extension  
2. Reopen demo page

Expected: Banner still works normally.

-----------------------------------------------------

End of manual test protocol.
